title: Squash/Rebase Commits Into One
tags: @zettel _method git
roam-id: 418adbb4-c77b-4f86-87b9-52a3eb34dbf5
type: text/markdown

I\'m squashing 4 commits before HEAD (HEAD included)

``` shell
git rebase -i HEAD~4
```

- leave the first commit as is but change the subsequent commits to `s`
- next, remove all the commit messages below and change the first one. or leave the first one as is.
- you can now do `git push --force` if you\'re sure about what you\'re doing
